MVM, magenta virtual machine

bytecode interpreter for magenta

0x |          |
---|----------|----------------------------------------------------------------
00 | push     | add to top of stack
01 | pop      | remove from top ofstack
02 | log      | read backwards from top of stack until null is reached, then p-
   |          | rint output
03 | clear    | remove all items from stack
---|----------|----------------------------------------------------------------
04 | mem set  | set address of memory
05 | mem add  | expand/allocate memory
06 | mem sub  | shrink/deallocate memory
07 | mem get  | get value at address and push to stack
---|----------|----------------------------------------------------------------
08 | add      | add two values and push answer to stack
09 | subtract | subtract two values from eachother and push answer to stack
0a | multiply | multiply two values and push answer to stack
0b | divide   | divide two values from eachother and push answer to stack
---|----------|----------------------------------------------------------------
0c | less     | if v0 is not less than v1 jump to v2
0d | less/eql | if v0 is not less than or equal to v1 jump to v2
0e | greater  | if v0 is not greater than v1 jump to v2
0f | grt/eql  | if v0 is not greater than or equal to v1 jump to v2
10 | equal    | if v0 is equal to v1 jump to v2
11 | jump     | jump to v0
---|----------|----------------------------------------------------------------
0x |          |